notesStmt.note: The last six leaves belonged to a different manuscript. Contain midrashic expositions on parashah Ṿa-yelekh and Ha᾿azinu.
Raḥamim ben Shemu᾿el Malkiowner: inscribed, folio 369r.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Parts of David ben Abraham Maimuni's homiletico-agadic commentary on Deuteronomy.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 21; written lines: 21; Catchwords (vertical, inclined) on every verso. Initial words given in larger characters. Running title on every recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental semi-cursive scripts of 17th century.The main scribe inscribed in the colophon as Yosef Motsri, folio 368v.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Black buckram, blind-tooled. Spine title: 'David ben Abraham. Comm. on Deuteronomy. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 70.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: A. C. Reichardt: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 June 1867: inscribed, folio [373v].
